comments: Morris Sr. (LAC) legally contests Kuzma's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Goodwin (WAS) is moving alongside Leonard's (LAC) path and he absorbs the contact at the end of the drive.
George (LAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Porzingis (WAS).
George (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.
George (LAC) makes contact with Porzingis' (WAS) arm as he is starting his upward shooting motion, and the contact affects his shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) is already in Avdija's (WAS) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Goodwin (WAS) briefly grasps and immediately releases Leonard's (LAC) jersey as they come together during the drive.
Goodwin (WAS) makes contact with the ball, and with the part of Leonard's (LAC) hand that is on the ball, as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Batum (LAC) is moving alongside Porzingis' (WAS) path and marginal contact occurs at the end of the drive.
Morris Sr. (LAC) is in the paint for longer than three seconds without imminently actively guarding an opponent.
Batum (LAC) turns slightly towards Avdija (WAS) and marginal contact occurs as the defenders switch.
Leonard (LAC) briefly grasps Avdija's (WAS) arm and marginal contact occurs as Leonard releases away to secure the pass.
Kuzma (WAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Leonard (LAC) legally contests Porzingis' (WAS) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
The crew communicated with the Replay Center and determined that the foul called on the Avdija (WAS) met the criteria for a flagrant foul.
Goodwin (WAS) commits a take foul on George (LAC).
Avdija (WAS) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.
